5	https://github.com/usestrix/strix	usestrix/strix:  Open-source AI hackers for your apps 	Skip to content Navigation Menu usestrix strix  Type / to search Code Issues 7 Pull requests 5 Actions Projects Security Insights  strix Public usestrix/strix  t Name    0xallam Update README b6d9d94  7 hours ago .github docs: Update README 4 days ago containers Running all agents under same container (#12) 3 months ago strix feat: add error handling for headless mode in agent execution and imp last week .gitignore Open-source release for Alpha version 3 months ago .pre-commit-config.yaml Open-source release for Alpha version 3 months ago CONTRIBUTING.md Chore: fix discord link in readme yesterday LICENSE Open-source release for Alpha version 3 months ago Makefile Open-source release for Alpha version 3 months ago README.md Update README 7 hours ago poetry.lock Fix: update litellm dependency version 3 days ago pyproject.toml Fix: update litellm dependency version 3 days ago Repository files navigation README Contributing Apache-2.0 license   Strix Open-source AI Hackers to secure your Apps             Love Strix? Give us a star to help other developers discover it!    Tip  New! Strix now integrates seamlessly with GitHub Actions and CI/CD pipelines. Automatically scan for vulnerabilities on every pull request and block insecure code before it reaches production!   Strix Overview Strix are autonomous AI agents that act just like real hackers - they run your code dynamically, find vulnerabilities, and validate them through actual proof-of-concepts. Built for developers and security teams who need fast, accurate security testing without the overhead of manual pentesting or the false positives of static analysis tools.  Full hacker toolkit out of the box Teams of agents that collaborate and scale Real validation with PoCs, not false positives Developerfirst CLI with actionable reports Autofix & reporting to accelerate remediation  Use Cases Detect and validate critical vulnerabili